---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { breadcrumbSchema } from '../data/seo';

const title = 'Privacy Policy | The Reflex Hub';
const description =
  'Read The Reflex Hub privacy policy: what we do not collect, how localStorage saves your scores, and how Google AdSense and analytics cookies work.';
const path = '/privacy-policy';

const schema = [
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'Privacy Policy', path },
  ]),
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} path={path} schema={schema}>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pt-10">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">Effective date: July 11, 2026</p>

    <article class="copy mt-6">
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        The Reflex Hub ("we", "us", or "the site") operates https://thereflexhub.com, a collection of free browser
        games that measure reaction time, clicking speed, typing speed, memory, and aim. This policy explains what
        information is and is not processed when you use the site, how advertising and analytics work, and the choices
        available to you. We designed the site to collect as little as possible: there are no accounts, no forms that
        gather personal details, and no server side profiles. By using the site, you agree to the practices described
        below.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
      <p>
        We do not ask for or store your name, email address, phone number, or any other personally identifiable
        information. There is no registration, no login, and no user database. We do not track your test scores on any
        server, we do not build behavioral profiles, and we never sell or share personal data, because we do not hold
        any. The only data connected with your use of the site lives either in your own browser (described in the next
        section) or in the aggregated, non identifying reports produced by the third party services described below.
      </p>

      <h2>Local Storage</h2>
      <p>
        The site uses localStorage, a standard feature of your web browser, to remember two kinds of things: your test
        results (personal bests and recent score history for each game) and your display preference (light or dark
        theme). This data is written and read entirely on your device. It is never transmitted to us or to anyone else,
        and it is not accessible to other websites. You can erase it at any time by clearing your browser's site data
        for thereflexhub.com, which will reset your saved scores and theme preference. Because the data lives only in
        one browser, scores do not sync across devices.
      </p>

      <h2>Advertising (Google AdSense)</h2>
      <p>
        The site displays advertisements served by Google AdSense to keep every test free. Google and its partners use
        cookies and similar technologies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this and other websites. In
        particular, Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to show you personalized ads. You
        can opt out of personalized advertising at any time:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Visit <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" rel="noopener nofollow">Google Ads Settings</a> to control how
          Google personalizes ads for you.
        </li>
        <li>
          Visit <a href="https://www.aboutads.info" rel="noopener nofollow">www.aboutads.info</a> to opt out of
          personalized ads from many third party vendors participating in the Digital Advertising Alliance.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Third party vendors and ad networks other than Google may also serve ads on this site. Where they do, their
        cookies are governed by their own privacy policies. If you prefer, you can block third party cookies entirely
        in your browser settings; the tests on this site will continue to work normally.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We use privacy friendly analytics (Plausible) to understand aggregate traffic: which pages are popular, roughly
        where visitors come from, and what devices they use. This analytics service does not use cookies, does not
        collect personal data, and does not track you across websites. Reports contain only anonymous, aggregated
        counts. We use them to decide which tests to improve and which content to write next, nothing more.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>
        Pages on this site may link to external websites, including the opt out resources listed above. We are not
        responsible for the content or privacy practices of other sites. When you follow a link away from
        thereflexhub.com, the destination site's own privacy policy applies, and we encourage you to review it.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The Reflex Hub is a general audience website and is not directed at children under 13 years of age. Consistent
        with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA), we do not knowingly collect personal information
        from children under 13, and because the site has no accounts or forms, no mechanism exists for a child to
        submit personal information to us. If you believe a child has somehow provided us with personal data, contact
        us and we will address it promptly.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, privacy laws such as the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the
        California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) grant you rights over personal data, including access, correction,
        deletion, and opting out of the sale of personal information. Because we do not collect or hold personal data
        ourselves, there is typically nothing for us to access or delete on your behalf. For data processed by Google
        for advertising, use the opt out tools linked in the Advertising section, or exercise your rights directly with
        Google. You can also clear your own localStorage data at any time through your browser.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time, for example if we change ad providers or add a new feature. When
        we do, we will revise the effective date at the top of this page. Material changes will be reflected here
        before they take effect, and continued use of the site after an update constitutes acceptance of the revised
        policy. We encourage you to review this page occasionally.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy or about privacy on The Reflex Hub? Reach out through our
        <a href="/contact">contact page</a> and we will get back to you as soon as we can.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
